{
  "stem": "13395.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I can only recall Jewish life before the war as seen through an eye of-- eyes of a child.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- I practically-- we just slept in our house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had a business there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we spent our life on the other side of the border, since our-- all-- entire family, except for my two grandmothers, was-- lived on the other side.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As I said before, this was all Germany at one time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My aunt lived in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And what I recall from the life of-- of our family, of our cousins and uncles and aunts, there were opportunities for German Jews in Germany, like there were for any other German.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was no difference.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "German Jews were members of the Berlin-- Berlin Philharmonics.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They would be artists, actors, doctors, professors, scientists, judges.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Before the Nazis, every door was open to Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Sure, there must have been anti-Semitism, but if you don't seek it, then it isn't there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There is anti-Semitism everywhere, but I have never heard of my family-- my-- or my parents talking about any discrimination.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Anything you wanted to be, it was open to you.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You want to go to university-- it wasn't like Poland, where they had numerous clauses where you couldn't attend university.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "German Jews wanted to go to the university, then it was there for them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They signed up, registered, just like any other German citizen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "German Jews fought in World War I.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My father was a decorated soldier, many of my mother's uncles.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We had some relatives that lost their lives during World War I and died for Germany, and who were decorated and were in high positions in government and so on.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
